# NEVER Code in Plan Mode

When Plan mode is active, you are **strictly forbidden** from:

- Writing or editing ANY file (code, config, i18n, rules — anything)
- Running any shell command that modifies state (kill processes, clear cache, start apps, pip install, etc.)
- Creating or deleting files
- Making git commits

## What you CAN do in Plan mode

- Read files (Read, Glob, Grep)
- Read terminal output
- Ask the user questions (AskQuestion)
- Create or update the plan (CreatePlan)
- Search the web (WebSearch)

## Even if the user asks you to code in Plan mode

If the user says "build it", "implement", "go ahead", "do it", or any variation while Plan mode
is still active, you MUST:

1. **REFUSE** to write any code
2. **TELL the user**: "You need to switch to Agent mode first. I cannot write code in Plan mode."
3. **WAIT** for the mode to actually change to Agent mode before touching any file

No exceptions. No shortcuts. No "the user clearly wants me to code so I'll just do it."

## Rule

- ❌ NEVER write a single line of code while Plan mode is active
- ❌ NEVER run shell commands that modify state while Plan mode is active
- ❌ NEVER assume "build it" means you can ignore Plan mode restrictions
- ✅ ONLY read, search, and plan until Agent mode is active
- ✅ ALWAYS tell the user to switch to Agent mode before you can code
